Andy Murray 'playing better' than ever after fourth Queen's title
Andy Murray believes he is "playing better" than ever after he wins his fourth Queen's Club titlewith an impressive victory over Kevin Anderson.The British number one played superbly to win 6-3 6-4 in just 64 minutes at the Aegon Championships in London.Murray says he has improved since his2013 Wimbledon triumph,but played down his chances of success at the All England Club by saying "there are no guarantees that winning here gives you a Wimbledon title".Available to UK viewers only